"'''Here with Me'''" is a song by [[Contemporary Christian music|Contemporary Christian]]/[[Christian rock]] band [[MercyMe]]. Written by the band, Peter Kipely, Dan Muckala and Brad Russell, the song is a [[ballad]] with a musical vibe influenced by [[Contemporary worship music|worship]], [[pop music|pop]] and [[rock music|rock]] music, and has been compared to the sound of [[Coldplay]] and [[Robbie Williams]]. It lyrically discusses the omnipotence of [[God in Christianity|God]].

Released as the [[lead single]] from MercyMe's 2004 album ''[[Undone (MercyMe album)|Undone]]'', "Here with Me" peaked at No. 1 on the [[Hot Christian Songs]], [[Hot Christian AC]], Christian AC, and Inspo charts. It also peaked at No. 2 on the Christian CHR chart, No. 12 on the [[Adult Contemporary (chart)|Adult Contemporary]] chart, and No. 38 on the [[Adult Top 40]] chart. It ranked at No. 4 on the 2004 year-end Hot Christian Singles and Tracks Titles and Hot Christian Adult Contemporary Titles charts, and No. 19 on the year-end Hot Adult Contemporary Singles and Tracks chart. It also ranked at No. 16 on the 2000s decade-end Hot Christian Songs and Hot Christian AC charts.

==Composition==
"Here with Me" is a [[ballad]]<ref name="Undone (Crosswalk.com)">{{cite web|url=http://www.crosswalk.com/culture/music/little-band-that-could-has-come-into-its-own-on-undone-1268817.html|title="Little Band That Could" Has Come into Its Own on "Undone"|last=McCreary|first=David|date=23 June 2004|work=[[CCM Magazine]]|publisher=[[Crosswalk.com]]|accessdate=14 October 2011}}</ref> with a length of four minutes and nine seconds.<ref name="Allmusic">{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/undone-r687579/review|title=Undone - MercyMe|last=Loftus|first=Johnny|publisher=Allmusic|accessdate=17 August 2011}}</ref> The song is set in [[common time]] in the key of [[B major]], with a moderate [[tempo]] of 84 beats per minute and a vocal range spanning from B<sub>3</sub>-F{{music|sharp}}<sub>5</sub>.<ref name="Musicnotes">{{cite web|url=http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtdVPE.asp?ppn=MN0049536|title=Here With Me Sheet Music|work=Musicnotes.com|publisher=Simpleville Music|accessdate=24 August 2011}}</ref>

Musically, the song has been compared to the musical vibe of [[Coldplay]]<ref name="A Severe Mercy">{{cite web|url=http://www.todayschristianmusic.com/artists/mercyme/features/a-severe-mercy/|title=A Severe Mercy|last=Jenison|first=David|work=[[Today's Christian Music]]|publisher=[[CCM Magazine]]|accessdate=14 October 2011}}</ref><ref name="Meet & Greet: MercyMe" /> and [[Robbie Williams]].<ref name="Allmusic" /> The song is piano-driven,<ref name="Undone (Crosswalk.com)" /> with influences from [[pop music|pop]],<ref name="Allmusic" /> [[rock music|rock]],<ref name="Meet & Greet: MercyMe">{{cite web|url=http://www.crosswalk.com/church/worship/meet-and-greet-mercyme-1263817.html|title=Meet & Greet: MercyMe|last=Nentwig|first=Wendy Lee Nentwig|date=20 May 2004|work=[[Crosswalk.com]]|accessdate=14 October 2011}}</ref> and [[Contemporary worship music|worship]].<ref name="A Severe Mercy" /><ref name="Meet & Greet: MercyMe" /> It features a musical [[crescendo]] that has been described as similar to "[[I Can Only Imagine]]".<ref name="Undone (Crosswalk.com)" />

The lyrical content of the song has been described as having a devotional bent,<ref name="Allmusic" /> and conveys a theme of [[God in Christianity|God]]'s omnipotence and holiness,<ref name="Undone (Crosswalk.com)" /> as well as trying to comprehend the mystery of his love.<ref name="Undone, Christian Music Reviews">{{cite web|url=http://www.thefish.com/music/reviews/11619121/Undone/|title=Undone, Christian Music Reviews|last=Breimeier|first=Russ|work=Christianity Today International|publisher=The Fish|accessdate=14 October 2011}}</ref>

==Reception==
===Critical reception===
"Here with Me" received generally positive reviews from critics. Johnny Joftus of [[Allmusic]] commented that "the lush "Here With Me" might be a Robbie Williams pop gem were it not for its devotional bent".<ref name="Allmusic" /> David McCreary of ''[[CCM Magazine]]'' opined on his review of ''[[Undone (MercyMe album)|Undone]]'' that "One surefire hit is <U+201C>Here With Me,<U+201D> the album<U+2019>s first single... A captivating piano-driven ballad, the song vividly conveys the wonder of God<U+2019>s omnipresence and holiness and features a rousing crescendo rivaling that of <U+201C>Imagine".<ref name="Undone (Crosswalk.com)" /> Russ Breimeier of ''Christianity Today International'' commented that the song was "worshipful",<ref name="Undone, Christian Music Reviews" /> also opining that the song "struggle[s] with comprehending the mystery and enormity of God's love".<ref name="Undone, Christian Music Reviews" />

===Chart performance===
"Here with Me" debuted at No. 40 on the [[Hot Christian Songs]] chart for the week of April 3, 2004.<ref name="Christian Songs Archive (3 April 2004)">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/#/charts/christian-songs?chartDate=2004-04-03&order=gainer|title=Christian Songs Archive (3 April 2004)|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=14 October 2011}}</ref><ref name="Here With Me - MercyMe (Billboard)">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/#/song/mercyme/here-with-me/5275575|title=Here With Me - MercyMe (Billboard)|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=14 October 2011}}</ref> The song advanced to No. 10 in its sixth chart week,<ref name="Here With Me - MercyMe (Billboard)" /><ref name="Christian Songs Archive (8 May 2004)">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/#/charts/christian-songs?chartDate=2004-05-08|title=Christian Songs Archive (8 May 2004)|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=14 October 2011}}</ref> and to No. 5 in its eight chart week, holding that spot for three consecutive weeks.<ref name="Here With Me - MercyMe (Billboard)" /><ref name="Christian Songs Archive (22 May 2004)">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/#/charts/christian-songs?chartDate=2004-05-22|title=Christian Songs Archive (22 May 2004)|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=14 October 2011}}</ref> In its sixteenth chart week, "Here with Me" advanced to No. 1,<ref name="Here With Me - MercyMe (Billboard)" /><ref name="Christian Songs Archive (17 July 2004)">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/#/charts/christian-songs?chartDate=2004-07-17|title=Christian Songs Archive (17 July 2004)|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=14 October 2011}}</ref> holding that spot for eleven consecutive weeks.<ref name="Here With Me - MercyMe (Billboard)" /> The song dropped to No. 2 in its twenty-seventh chart week,<ref name="Here With Me - MercyMe (Billboard)" /><ref name="Christian Songs Archive (2 October 2004)">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/#/charts/christian-songs?chartDate=2004-10-02|title=Christian Songs Archive (2 October 2004)|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=14 October 2011}}</ref> holding that spot for eleven consecutive weeks.<ref name="Here With Me - MercyMe (Billboard)" /> holding that spot for two weeks before returning to No. 1 for two more weeks.<ref name="Here With Me - MercyMe (Billboard)" /> "Here with Me" dropped to No. 3 in its thirty-first chart week,<ref name="Here With Me - MercyMe (Billboard)" /><ref name="Christian Songs Archive (30 October 2004)">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/#/charts/christian-songs?chartDate=2004-10-30|title=Christian Songs Archive (30 October 2004)|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=14 October 2011}}</ref> and spent a further eight weeks on the chart before dropping out.<ref name="Here With Me - MercyMe (Billboard)" /> In all, "Here with Me" spent thirty-nine weeks on the Hot Christian Songs chart, thirteen of them at No. 1.<ref name="Here With Me - MercyMe (Billboard)" />

On the [[Adult Contemporary (chart)|Adult Contemporary]] chart, "Here with Me" debuted at No. 24 for the chart week of May 15, 2004.<ref name="Here With Me - MercyMe (Billboard)" /><ref name="Adult Contemporary Archive (15 May 2004)">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/#/charts/adult-contemporary?chartDate=2004-05-15&order=gainer|title=Adult Contemporary Archive (15 May 2004)|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=14 October 2011}}</ref> "Here with Me" advanced to No. 19 in its sixth chart week, holding that spot for three consecutive weeks.<ref name="Here With Me - MercyMe (Billboard)" /> In its nineteenth chart week, the song advanced to its peak of No. 12, and spent a further seven weeks on the chart before dropping out.<ref name="Here With Me - MercyMe (Billboard)" /> In all, "Here with Me" spent twenty-six weeks on the Adult Contemporary chart.<ref name="Here With Me - MercyMe (Billboard)" />

On the [[Adult Top 40]] chart, "Here with Me" debuted at No. 38 for the chart week of August 28, 2004.<ref name="Here With Me - MercyMe (Billboard)" /> The song spent an additional week on the chart before dropping out, after having spent two weeks on the chart.<ref name="Here With Me - MercyMe (Billboard)" /> "Here with Me" also peaked at No. 1 on the ''Billboard'' [[Hot Christian AC]] chart (spending ten weeks at No. 1),<ref name="Charted Singles" /> the ''[[Radio & Records]]'' Christian AC chart (spending seven weeks at No. 1),<ref name="Charted Singles" /> and the ''Radio & Records'' Inspo chart (spending five weeks at No. 1),<ref name="Charted Singles" /> as well as peaking at No. 2 on the ''Radio & Records'' Christian CHR chart.<ref name="Charted Singles" />

"Here with Me" ranked at No. 4 on the 2004 year-end Hot Christian Singles and Tracks Titles<ref name="Hot Christian Singles and Tracks Titles Year-end (2004)" /> and Hot Christian Adult Contemporary Titles charts,<ref name="Hot Christian Adult Contemporary Titles Year-end (2004)" /> as well as at No. 19 on the year-end Adult Contemporary Singles and Tracks chart.<ref name="Hot Adult Contemporary Year-end (2004)" /> Additionally, it ranked at No. 4 on both the 2000s decade-end Hot Christian Songs<ref name="Hot Christian Songs (Decade-end)" /> and Hot Christian AC charts.<ref name="Hot Christian AC (Decade-end)" />

